<plot>A hotel arson fire, with a man named Al Russell's body found inside -- knifed in the back. Kenny Jason is identified in the crowd by the room-clerk. Former police captain, now attorney Matthew Considine, defends him. Is he guilty? Considine may get him acquitted on murder, but what about an arson charge? Or another murder charge of a witness??</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?200057</url></doc>
